    text: `You are a level design lead designing one map to support three modes in a 5v5 competitive game: team deathmatch (symmetric spawns, no objectives), hardpoint control (3 rotating capture zones needing distinct approach angles), and search-and-destroy (2 bombsites, attacker/defender asymmetry, no respawn). TDM wants symmetric flow. S&D wants structural asymmetry. These requirements directly conflict. Design the base geometry that serves all three. Specify: the 3 mode-specific elements that toggle per mode (name them and what they do in each mode), the one flow element that is non-negotiable across all three modes and why, and which mode you compromise on -- state the specific mechanic or flow property you sacrifice and how you communicate this compromise to the game design leads of the affected modes. Then name the one spatial feature that actually improves all three modes despite the conflict, and explain why.`
